tl;dr

cmake >= 3.20.2
gcc   >= 6.1.0


cmake
    SDL uses cmake and may well be able to tolerate older versions in a
    stand-alone build.  Nanopond uses the --prefix and -j options for
    --install and --build, respectively, and the former needs a more
    recent version.

    Versions known to work.
    3.23.1
    3.22.4
    3.21.1
    3.20.2

    Versions known NOT to work:
    3.18.0
    3.16.8

gcc
    SDL assumes -std=c99, which requires 5.5+.

    Versions known to work
    10.2.1 20200804 (Red Hat 10.2.1-2)
    9.3.1 20200408 (Red Hat 9.3.1-2)
    8.3.1 20190311 (Red Hat 8.3.1-3)
    7.3.0
    6.1.0

    Versions known NOT to work
    4.9.3
